==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hustle
<hw>Hus"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Hustled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hustling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[D.
<ets>hustelen</ets> to shake, fr. <ets>husten</ets> to shake. Cf.
<er>Hotchpotch</er>.]</ety> <def>To shake together in confusion; to
push, jostle, or crowd rudely; to handle roughly; <as>as, to
<ex>hustle</ex> a person out of a room</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hustle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hustle
<hw>Hus"tle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To push or crows; to force one's
way; to move hastily and with confusion; a hurry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Leaving the king, who had <qex>hustled</qex> along the floor with
his dress worfully arrayed.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Huswife</ent>⟦br⟧
